---
description: PHP tools intended for CLI-only use must refuse web execution and print a clear error message
globs: tools/**/*.php
alwaysApply: false
---

- **Tools that are intended to be CLI-only MUST explicitly refuse web execution**
  - This avoids accidental DB writes and keeps “maintenance scripts” out of browser context.
  - Canonical pattern exists in [V:\tools\repeatable\backfill_character_biography.php](mdc:tools/repeatable/backfill_character_biography.php) lines 30-34.

```php
$is_cli = php_sapi_name() === 'cli';
if (!$is_cli) {
    die("This script must be run from the command line.\n");
}
```

- **CLI-only tools MUST provide `--help` output**
  - Include a short usage block and list of supported flags (example in `backfill_character_biography.php` lines 56-65).

- **If a tool needs both CLI and web, it MUST follow the hybrid pattern**
  - See: [php-tools-that-support-cli-and-web-must-detect-php_sapi_name-and-format-output-accordingly.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/php-tools-that-support-cli-and-web-must-detect-php_sapi_name-and-format-output-accordingly.mdc)
